* These next two routines change the RS-232 line and can't have any use in the game.
* They do interfere with DW4 so I've changed them to toggle the single bit sound as
* that might just make some sense. Also no timing changes will result by switching to
* $FF22. RG
sound_line_enable                     pshs      a                                         ; preserve a across the following sound line enable work.
                                      lda       >$FF22                                    ; fetch $FF22 for the sound line enable calculation.
                                      anda      #$FD                                      ; apply the constant $FD mask/flags required by sound line enable.
                                      sta       >$FF22                                    ; commit the updated sound line enable value to $FF22.
                                      puls      a                                         ; restore a; including PC returns when requested.
                                      rts                                                 ; return the completed sound line enable result to the caller.
